THORAX AND ABDOMEN. Body length 4.20–5.30 mm (see
Table. 1
), elongate (
Fig. 52
). Abdominal segments I– V almost equal in length, slightly larger than abdominal segment VI and VII (
Fig. 52
). Spiracles on abdomen in median parts of segments (abdominal seg. I–VIII).

MORPHOLOGY (
Figs. 56–60
). Body length 2.95–3.90 mm ; widest part 1.90–2.40 mm (see
Table. 2
). Body moderately stout. Rostrum long, approximately 5 times as long as wide, reaching mesocoxae. Pronotum 1.85 times as wide as long.

CHAETOTAXY (
Figs. 56–60
). Setae distinct, short to moderately long, unequal in length, light brown, on head, rostrum and thorax hair-like, on abdomen almost as thorn-like. Sos and pas slightly shorter than other setae of head and rostrum (
Fig. 57
). All pronotal setae moderately long and equal in length (
Fig. 59
). Setae on abdominal segments I–VIII located posteromedially and posterolaterally; all abdominal setae short, curved, located on thornlike protuberances. Pseudocerci elongated, slightly curved to inside.
